{"title_page": "East Fishkill, New York", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                     = East Fishkill, New York\n|settlement_type          = [[Town (New York)|Town]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = Bykenhulle, Hopewell Junction, NY.jpg\n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = [[Bykenhulle]] House Historic Site\n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               = Seal of East Fishkill, New York.png\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n||pushpin_map            = \n|pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|pushpin_mapsize        = \n|image_map                = Dutchess County New York incorporated areas East Fishkill highlighted.svg\n|mapsize                  = 220px\n|map_caption              = Location of East Fishkill, New York\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[New York (state)|New York]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in New York|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Dutchess County, New York|Dutchess]]\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = [[Town Council]]\n|leader_title             = [[Town Supervisor]]\n|leader_name              = Nicholas D'Alessandro ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]])\n| leader_title2           = [[Town Council]]\n| leader_name2            = {{Collapsible list\n |title       = Anil R. Beephan Jr. (R,C,I)\n |frame_style = border:none; padding: 0;\n |title_style = <!-- (optional) -->\n |list_style  = text-align:left;display:none;\n |1           = \u2022 Peter Cassidy ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]])\n |2           = \u2022 Thomas Franco ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]])\n |3           = \u2022 Emanuele Marinaro ([[Conservative Party of New York State|C]])\n}}\n|established_title        = Established\n|established_date         = 1849\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|unit_pref  = Imperial\n|area_footnotes           = <ref name=\"CenPopGazetteer2016\">{{cite web|title=2016 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2016_Gazetteer/2016_gaz_place_36.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=Jul 4, 2017}}</ref>\n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 148.63\n|area_land_km2            = 146.35\n|area_water_km2           = 2.29\n|area_total_sq_mi         = 57.39\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 56.50\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 0.88\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_total         = 29029\n|population_density_km2   = 201.16\n|population_density_sq_mi = 521.01\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone                 = [[North American Eastern Time Zone|Eastern (EST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -5\n|timezone_DST             = EDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -4\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 88\n|elevation_ft             = 289\n|coordinates              = {{coord|41|34|N|73|48|W|region:US-NY|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP Code]]s\n|postal_code              = 12533, 12590, 12582 (There is no ZIP for East Fishkill. USPS addressing is split between Hopewell Junction, Stormville and Wappingers Falls)\n|area_code                = [[Area code 845|845]]\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standards|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 36-027-21996\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = 0978917\n|website                  = {{URL|eastfishkillny.org}}\n|footnotes                = \n|pop_est_as_of = 2016\n|pop_est_footnotes = <ref name=\"USCensusEst2016\"/>\n|population_est = 29439\n}}\n'''East Fishkill''' is a [[Town (New York)|town]] on the southern border of [[Dutchess County, New York|Dutchess County]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States. The population was 29,029 at the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]].<ref name=\"Census 2010\">{{cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/G001/0600000US3602721996| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): East Fishkill town, Dutchess County, New York| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=November 12, 2015| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213123655/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/G001/0600000US3602721996| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref> The town was once the eastern portion of the town of [[Fishkill (town), New York|Fishkill]].\n\nHudson Valley Research Park (formerly known as IBM East Fishkill) is located in the town, and housed 27 divisions and 4,700 regular employees for [[IBM]] Microelectronics, which GlobalFoundries bought. While IBM produced microchips they owned the advanced, automated processor [[semiconductor fabrication plant|fabrication facility]] where IBM's \"[[Cell (microprocessor)|Cell]]\" processor was co-developed.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Storm-Adriance-Brinckerhoff House.jpg|thumb|left|The [[Storm-Adriance-Brinckerhoff House]], built in 1759]]\nOne early settler arrived around 1759. The town of East Fishkill was established in 1849 from the eastern part of the town of [[Fishkill (town), New York|Fishkill]]. Its name comes from [[Fishkill Creek]], known as the ''Vis Kill'' (Fish Creek) to the  Dutch settlers in the area.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/ffi23| title=Fisher County| publisher=Texas State Historical Association| accessdate=2012-05-24| author=Hooper Shelton}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the town has a total area of {{convert|148.6|km2|order=flip}}, of which {{convert|146.3|km2|order=flip}} is land and {{convert|2.3|km2|order=flip}}, or 1.54%, is water.<ref name=\"Census 2010\"/>\n\nEast Fishkill is bordered on the west by [[Fishkill (town), New York|Fishkill]] and [[Wappinger, New York|Wappinger]], on the north by [[LaGrange, New York|LaGrange]], and on the east by [[Beekman, New York|Beekman]] and [[Pawling (town), New York|Pawling]]. The south town line borders [[Philipstown, New York|Philipstown]] and [[Kent, New York|Kent]], both of which are part of [[Putnam County, New York|Putnam County]].\n\n[[Interstate 84 in New York|Interstate 84]] and the [[Appalachian Trail]] pass across the town. The [[Taconic State Parkway]] runs north-south as well.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1850= 2610\n|1860= 2544\n|1870= 2305\n|1880= 2574\n|1890= 2175\n|1900= 1970\n|1910= 2226\n|1920= 1944\n|1930= 1845\n|1940= 2024\n|1950= 2565\n|1960= 4778\n|1970= 11092\n|1980= 18091\n|1990= 22101\n|2000= 25589\n|2010= 29029\n|estyear=2016\n|estimate=29439\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2016.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|website=Census.gov|accessdate=June 9, 2017}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|website=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\nAs of the [[census]] of 2000, there were 25,589 people, 8,233 households, and 7,006 families residing in the town.  The [[population density]] was 449.7 people per square mile (173.6/km\u00b2).  There were 8,495 housing units at an average density of 149.3 per square mile (57.6/km\u00b2).  The racial makeup of the town was 92.54% [[White (U.S. Census)|white]], 2.29% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.15% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2.80% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.02% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.86% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.34% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 4.04% of the population.\n\nThere were 8,233 households out of which 45.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 75.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 6.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 14.9% were non-families. Of all households 11.9% were made up of individuals and 3.9% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 3.10 and the average family size was 3.38.\n\nIn the town, the population was spread out with 29.7% under the age of 18, 6.4% from 18 to 24, 30.4% from 25 to 44, 25.5% from 45 to 64, and 8.0% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 37 years. For every 100 females, there were 98.9 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 96.9 males.\n\nThe mean income for a household in the town was $116,059, and the mean income for a family was $129,660.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid%3DACS_11_5YR_DP03 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=March 17, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20190405142507/http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_11_5YR_DP03 |archivedate=April 5, 2019 }}</ref> Males had a median income of $59,735 versus $35,014 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $28,553.  About 1.5% of families and 2.8% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 2.7% of those under age 18 and 3.7% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==Locations==\n* East Fishkill &ndash; A hamlet.\n* Fishkill Plains &ndash; A hamlet in the northwest part of the town.\n* Gayhead &ndash; A location south of East Fishkill hamlet.\n* [[Green Haven Correctional Facility]] &ndash; A maximum security prison that is located in the town of Beekman\n* [[Hillside Lake, New York|Hillside Lake]] &ndash; A location northeast of Fishkill Plains.\n* [[Hopewell Junction, New York|Hopewell Junction]] &ndash; A hamlet in the northwest part of the town.\n* Hortontown &ndash; A hamlet in the eastern part.\n* Leetown - An area on top of Stormville Mountain, named after early settlers. \n* The Ville - The Ville is a name derived from Stormville, the hamlet where The Ville is located in. It is known for its secluded forests, and Kiyiwana Farm.\n* Johnsville &ndash; A hamlet near the west border.\n* Lomala &ndash; A hamlet south of Hopewell Junction.\n* Pecksville &ndash; A hamlet in the southeast corner of the town.\n* Shenandoah Corners &ndash; A hamlet in the south part of the town.\n* Stormville &ndash; A hamlet in the eastern part of the town named after early settlers, brothers Jacob and Rupert Storm.\n* Wiccopee &ndash; A hamlet near the west town line.\n\n==See also==\n* {{Portal-inline|Hudson Valley}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|East Fishkill, New York}}\n* [http://www.eastfishkillny.org/ Town of East Fishkill official website]\n* [http://www.eastfishkillhistoricalsociety.org East Fishkill Historical Society]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X1oMCVZZi0s \"Historic Hopewell Junction\" video (includes East Fishkill)]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20091016202558/http://fishkillcreekwatershed.org/ Fishkill Creek Watershed Association]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160308224850/http://eastfishkillfiredistrict.org/ East Fishkill Fire District]\n* [http://www.eastfishkilllibrary.org/ East Fishkill Community Library]\n\n{{Dutchess County, New York}}\n{{Hudson River}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Towns in Dutchess County, New York]]\n[[Category:Towns in the New York metropolitan area|Dutchess]]\n[[Category:Dutch place names in New York (state)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                     = East Fishkill, New York\n|settlement_type          = [[Town (New York)|Town]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = Bykenhulle, Hopewell Junction, NY.jpg\n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = [[Bykenhulle]] House Historic Site\n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               = Seal of East Fishkill, New York.png\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n||pushpin_map            = \n|pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|pushpin_mapsize        = \n|image_map                = Dutchess County New York incorporated areas East Fishkill highlighted.svg\n|mapsize                  = 220px\n|map_caption              = Location of East Fishkill, New York\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[New York (state)|New York]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in New York|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Dutchess County, New York|Dutchess]]\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = [[Town Council]]\n|leader_title             = [[Town Supervisor]]\n|leader_name              = Nicholas D'Alessandro ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]])\n| leader_title2           = [[Town Council]]\n| leader_name2            = {{Collapsible list\n |title       = Anil R. Beephan Jr. (R,C,I)\n |frame_style = border:none; padding: 0;\n |title_style = <!-- (optional) -->\n |list_style  = text-align:left;display:none;\n |1           = \u2022 Peter Cassidy ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]])\n |2           = \u2022 Thomas Franco ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]])\n |3           = \u2022 Emanuele Marinaro ([[Conservative Party of New York State|C]])\n}}\n|established_title        = Established\n|established_date         = 1849\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|unit_pref  = Imperial\n|area_footnotes           = <ref name=\"CenPopGazetteer2016\">{{cite web|title=2016 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2016_Gazetteer/2016_gaz_place_36.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=Jul 4, 2017}}</ref>\n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 148.63\n|area_land_km2            = 146.35\n|area_water_km2           = 2.29\n|area_total_sq_mi         = 57.39\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 56.50\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 0.88\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_total         = 29029\n|population_density_km2   = 201.16\n|population_density_sq_mi = 521.01\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone                 = [[North American Eastern Time Zone|Eastern (EST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -5\n|timezone_DST             = EDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -4\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 88\n|elevation_ft             = 289\n|coordinates              = {{coord|41|34|N|73|48|W|region:US-NY|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP Code]]s\n|postal_code              = 12533, 12590, 12582 (There is no ZIP for East Fishkill. USPS addressing is split between Hopewell Junction, Stormville and Wappingers Falls)\n|area_code                = [[Area code 845|845]]\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standards|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 36-027-21996\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = 0978917\n|website                  = {{URL|eastfishkillny.org}}\n|footnotes                = \n|pop_est_as_of = 2016\n|pop_est_footnotes = <ref name=\"USCensusEst2016\"/>\n|population_est = 29439\n}}\n'''East Fishkill''' is a [[Town (New York)|town]] on the southern border of [[Dutchess County, New York|Dutchess County]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States. The population was 29,029 at the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]].<ref name=\"Census 2010\">{{cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/G001/0600000US3602721996| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): East Fishkill town, Dutchess County, New York| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=November 12, 2015| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213123655/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/G001/0600000US3602721996| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref> The town was once the eastern portion of the town of [[Fishkill (town), New York|Fishkill]].\n\nHudson Valley Research Park (formerly known as IBM East Fishkill) is located in the town, and housed 27 divisions and 4,700 regular employees for [[IBM]] Microelectronics, which GlobalFoundries bought. While IBM produced microchips they owned the advanced, automated processor [[semiconductor fabrication plant|fabrication facility]] where IBM's \"[[Cell (microprocessor)|Cell]]\" processor was co-developed.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Storm-Adriance-Brinckerhoff House.jpg|thumb|left|The [[Storm-Adriance-Brinckerhoff House]], built in 1759]]\nOne early settler arrived around 1759. The town of East Fishkill was established in 1849 from the eastern part of the town of [[Fishkill (town), New York|Fishkill]]. Its name comes from [[Fishkill Creek]], known as the ''Vis Kill'' (Fish Creek) to the  Dutch settlers in the area.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/ffi23| title=Fisher County| publisher=Texas State Historical Association| accessdate=2012-05-24| author=Hooper Shelton}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the town has a total area of {{convert|148.6|km2|order=flip}}, of which {{convert|146.3|km2|order=flip}} is land and {{convert|2.3|km2|order=flip}}, or 1.54%, is water.<ref name=\"Census 2010\"/>\n\nEast Fishkill is bordered on the west by [[Fishkill (town), New York|Fishkill]] and [[Wappinger, New York|Wappinger]], on the north by [[La Grange, New York|La Grange]], and on the east by [[Beekman, New York|Beekman]] and [[Pawling (town), New York|Pawling]]. The south town line borders [[Philipstown, New York|Philipstown]] and [[Kent, New York|Kent]], both of which are part of [[Putnam County, New York|Putnam County]].\n\n[[Interstate 84 in New York|Interstate 84]] and the [[Appalachian Trail]] pass across the town. The [[Taconic State Parkway]] runs north-south as well.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1850= 2610\n|1860= 2544\n|1870= 2305\n|1880= 2574\n|1890= 2175\n|1900= 1970\n|1910= 2226\n|1920= 1944\n|1930= 1845\n|1940= 2024\n|1950= 2565\n|1960= 4778\n|1970= 11092\n|1980= 18091\n|1990= 22101\n|2000= 25589\n|2010= 29029\n|estyear=2016\n|estimate=29439\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2016.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|website=Census.gov|accessdate=June 9, 2017}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|website=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\nAs of the [[census]] of 2000, there were 25,589 people, 8,233 households, and 7,006 families residing in the town.  The [[population density]] was 449.7 people per square mile (173.6/km\u00b2).  There were 8,495 housing units at an average density of 149.3 per square mile (57.6/km\u00b2).  The racial makeup of the town was 92.54% [[White (U.S. Census)|white]], 2.29% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.15% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2.80% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.02% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.86% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.34% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 4.04% of the population.\n\nThere were 8,233 households out of which 45.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 75.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 6.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 14.9% were non-families. Of all households 11.9% were made up of individuals and 3.9% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 3.10 and the average family size was 3.38.\n\nIn the town, the population was spread out with 29.7% under the age of 18, 6.4% from 18 to 24, 30.4% from 25 to 44, 25.5% from 45 to 64, and 8.0% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 37 years. For every 100 females, there were 98.9 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 96.9 males.\n\nThe mean income for a household in the town was $116,059, and the mean income for a family was $129,660.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid%3DACS_11_5YR_DP03 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=March 17, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20190405142507/http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_11_5YR_DP03 |archivedate=April 5, 2019 }}</ref> Males had a median income of $59,735 versus $35,014 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $28,553.  About 1.5% of families and 2.8% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 2.7% of those under age 18 and 3.7% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==Locations==\n* East Fishkill &ndash; A hamlet.\n* Fishkill Plains &ndash; A hamlet in the northwest part of the town.\n* Gayhead &ndash; A location south of East Fishkill hamlet.\n* [[Green Haven Correctional Facility]] &ndash; A maximum security prison that is located in the town of Beekman\n* [[Hillside Lake, New York|Hillside Lake]] &ndash; A location northeast of Fishkill Plains.\n* [[Hopewell Junction, New York|Hopewell Junction]] &ndash; A hamlet in the northwest part of the town.\n* Hortontown &ndash; A hamlet in the eastern part.\n* Leetown - An area on top of Stormville Mountain, named after early settlers. \n* The Ville - The Ville is a name derived from Stormville, the hamlet where The Ville is located in. It is known for its secluded forests, and Kiyiwana Farm.\n* Johnsville &ndash; A hamlet near the west border.\n* Lomala &ndash; A hamlet south of Hopewell Junction.\n* Pecksville &ndash; A hamlet in the southeast corner of the town.\n* Shenandoah Corners &ndash; A hamlet in the south part of the town.\n* Stormville &ndash; A hamlet in the eastern part of the town named after early settlers, brothers Jacob and Rupert Storm.\n* Wiccopee &ndash; A hamlet near the west town line.\n\n==See also==\n* {{Portal-inline|Hudson Valley}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|East Fishkill, New York}}\n* [http://www.eastfishkillny.org/ Town of East Fishkill official website]\n* [http://www.eastfishkillhistoricalsociety.org East Fishkill Historical Society]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X1oMCVZZi0s \"Historic Hopewell Junction\" video (includes East Fishkill)]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20091016202558/http://fishkillcreekwatershed.org/ Fishkill Creek Watershed Association]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160308224850/http://eastfishkillfiredistrict.org/ East Fishkill Fire District]\n* [http://www.eastfishkilllibrary.org/ East Fishkill Community Library]\n\n{{Dutchess County, New York}}\n{{Hudson River}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Towns in Dutchess County, New York]]\n[[Category:Towns in the New York metropolitan area|Dutchess]]\n[[Category:Dutch place names in New York (state)]]\n", "name_user": "Spacemace1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGeography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Fishkill,_New_York"}
{"title_page": "Andrew Roettger", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name         = Versatile\n| background   = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name   = Andrew Roettger\n| alias        =  \n| origin       = [[New Jersey]], [[United States]]\n| image        = \n| caption      = \n| image_size   =\n| instrument   =\n| genre        = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]], [[R&B]]\n| occupation   = [[Record producer]], [[songwriter]], remixer\n| years_active = 2006&ndash;present\n| label        = BMG Publishing, Versatile Music LLC\n}}\n\n'''Andrew Roettger''', better known as '''Versatile''', is an [[United States|American]] record producer, songwriter, and remixer from [[New Jersey]]. Versatile is signed to BMG Publishing and has his own company Versatile Music LLC.<ref name=\"redorbit\">[http://www.redorbit.com/news/entertainment/1691051/music_industry_heavyweights_gather_in_miami_hoping_to_discover_the/ Music Industry Heavyweights Gather in Miami; Hoping to Discover the \u2018Next Big Thing\u2019]</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Versatile BMG Profile Page|url=http://bmg.com/category/music/?artist=versatile|accessdate=14 November 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130118042749/http://bmg.com/category/music/?artist=versatile|archive-date=18 January 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nVersatile has produced and remixed for artists like [[Chris Brown (American entertainer)|Chris Brown]], [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]], [[Fabolous]], [[Jay-Z]], [[Maino]], [[Ciara]], [[Britney Spears]], [[Joe Budden]], [[Slimmie Hendrix|Pittsburgh Slim]], [[Nelly]], [[Nelly Furtado]], amongst others.<ref name=\"redorbit\"/><ref>[http://www.parcitizens.com/2011/04/featurefridays-par-city-featuring.html Parcitizens:  Par-City Featuring Panama - \"Hey, Hey, Hey\" (prod. by Versatile)]</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Versatile- Producer for Fabolous, Method Man, & more|url=http://blog.istandardproducers.com/2009/05/versatile-producer-for-fabolous-method-m